.Dd August 6, 1998
.Dt MIDI 4
.Os NetBSD
.Sh NAME
.Nm midi
.Nd device-independent MIDI driver layer
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <sys/types.h>
.Fd #include <sys/midiio.h>
.Sh CONFIGURATION
.Cd "midi* at XX"
.Cd "pseudo-device sequencer"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
driver provides support for various MIDI peripherals.
It provides a uniform programming interface layer above different
underlying MIDI hardware drivers.
.Pp
There are three device file types available for MIDI operation:
.Pa /dev/rmidiN ,
.Pa /dev/music ,
and
.Pa /dev/sequencer .
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width /dev/sequencer -compact
.It Pa /dev/rmidiN
.It Pa /dev/music
.It Pa /dev/sequencer
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr audio 4 ,
.Xr ioctl 2 ,
.Xr ossaudio 3 .
.br
For ports using the ISA bus:
.Xr sb 4 .
.Sh BUGS
This man page is very incomplete.
.Pp
